conbody.p: Create a 2D or 3D spline that is open or closed. Options allow you to specify start and end points, fit points, and tangencies.

section.title: Methods to create a spline
section.p: There is one method to begin creating a spline:
You can continue adding unlimited points until you press Enter to end the command.

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a spline by specifying the start point then:
Specify a tangency for the starting point or press Enter to ignore this option.
Specify a tangency for the ending point or press Enter to ignore this option.

section.title: Additional options within the SPLINE command
section.p: After you begin creating a spline, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Automatically draw a spline segment between the start and end points to create a closed spline.
Specify (in drawing units) how closely the spline matches its fit points. If the fit tolerance is 0, the spline passes through its fit points.
Undo the last fit point and continue drawing from the previous fit point.
